>>d86088c0-2775-4977-8782-eecfe06e3d6e
>I expect certain groups would begin publishing lists of spamIds and a global policy of muting them by all seeders would develop
Yes. I call this "mod streams". I think we should begin to implement this functionality right now and not when we're under attack and can't even coordinate effectively.
The power of blacklisting shouldn't rely only on the site owner. Mainly because he's not necessarily the entity with most amount of resources (free time basically) to tag spam posts, but also because some other people might not consider spam some of what he decides to blacklist. You can disable blacklists, but then you have to look at ALL the blacklisted stuff that was ever posted, even if you would consider some particular post spam too. This wouldn't be an issue with mod streams that could be subscribed to by the user and would implement certain policies aligned with the user.
Anyone who wants to contribute to development probably should begin here https://zeronet.io/docs/site_development/zeroframe_api_reference/ (after updating his install to the latest version of Millchan to familiarize himself with how the software works).
